1.00	Association_of_religion_data_archives	Association of Religion Data Archives	The Association of Religion Data Archives (ARDA) is a free source of online information related to American and international religion. Founded as the American Religion Data Archive in 1997, and online since 1998, the archive was initially targeted at researchers interested in American religion. One of the primary goals of the archive is to democratize access to quality information on religion by making this information as widely accessible as possible.	
